cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with substructural calculi and proof theory. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses cost-conscious reasoning, which is relevant to AI applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper introduces a new kind of labelled calculus. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the cost of different proofs and strategies. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a semiring structure to generalize the concept of costs in proofs.
